(AP Photo/LM Otero) Posted: Sunday, October 4, 2015 6:13 pm Rangers win AL West on final day, Hamels beat Angels 9-2 Associated Press | 
ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) â€” Cole Hamels and the Texas Rangers finally clinched the AL West title on the last day of the regular season. 
Hamels pitched a three-hitter, Adrian Beltre hit a go-ahead homer and the Rangers beat the Angels 9-2 Sunday, eliminating Los Angeles from playoff contention.
